Reasoning: The paper deals with the study of cellular automata, which is a topic that falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of ultimate trace involves the long-term behavior of the automata, which can be analyzed using information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the undecidability of certain properties, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the study of cellular automata has applications in formal languages (cs.FL) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
